UPDATE Language_en_US
SET Text = 'Founded by the Portuguese in 1565, Rio de Janeiro quickly became one of the most important cities in Brazil due to its strategic location along the Atlantic coast. Originally established as a defensive settlement against French incursions, Rio grew into a thriving port city, benefiting from the lucrative trade in sugar, gold, and later, coffee. By the 18th century, it had become the capital of colonial Brazil.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]During the early 19th century, Rio de Janeiro gained global prominence when the Portuguese royal court fled to the city to escape Napoleon''s invasion of Portugal. This unprecedented move transformed Rio into the capital of the Portuguese Empire, fostering significant urban and cultural development. Even after Brazil''s independence in 1822, the city remained the nation''s capital until 1960, when the government relocated to Brasília.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Today, Rio de Janeiro is one of Brazil''s most vibrant cities, famous for its stunning beaches, iconic landmarks like Christ the Redeemer, and the world-renowned Carnival festival. Despite challenges related to urbanization, it remains a major cultural and economic hub in South America.'
WHERE Tag = 'TXT_KEY_CIV5_RIODEJANEIRO_TEXT';